  "text": "Genotypes HEV-3 and 4 are zoonotic pathogens infecting domestic (e.g., pigs) and wild animal species (e.g., boars, deers) which constitute the animal reservoir [CITATION_1] . They are mainly detected in industrialized countries and are responsible for sporadic and autochthonous cases [1, [CITATION_2] . In Europe, the majority of cases is due to HEV-3 genotype and HEV is the most common cause of acute viral hepatitis [CITATION_3] .",
